==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sartorius
<hw>Sar*to"ri*us</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>sartor</ets> a patcher, tailor, fr. <ets>sarcire</ets>,
<ets>sartum</ets>, to patch, mend.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A
muscle of the thigh, called the <xex>tailor's muscle</xex>, which arises
from the hip bone and is inserted just below the knee. So named because
its contraction was supposed to produce the position of the legs assumed
by the tailor in sitting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sarum use</ent>⟦br⟧
